**Summary:** This Japanese documentation explains how to configure Amplitude's schema settings to handle three types of schema violations: unplanned event types, unplanned event/user properties, and unplanned property values, with options to accept/auto-add to schema, trigger warnings, or reject data, plus viewing validation errors in the validation panel.

